<dl id="n42007e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n42" href="#n42007e">N42 (VI.B.31)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n42all.htm#n42007e"> 7(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> shake off her shame <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n42007e"><li>FW 188.22 </li><li><a href="../../flex/g/lexg.htm#n42007e">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/g/l39g.htm#n42007e">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n42007e">MS BL 47475-72</ms> </li><li>JJA 47:512 <a name="gd9" href="../../ff/fdra/gda.htm#gd9">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/g/gd9.htm#n42007e">Draft: I.7&sect;1.9</a>/2.9</li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">When I saw myself alone, under the irresistible impression that this was her last day, I fell on my knees again, and with tears of the most sincere compassion for her soul, I requested her to shake off her shame and to obey our holy Church, which requires everyone to confess their sins if they want to be forgiven. <small> Chiniquy, <a name="CPWC" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#CPWC"><cite title="source">The Priest The Woman and The Confessional</cite></a> (n.d.) 19</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
